  "name": "Pneumonia - Diagnosis Code Query (Multi-Etiology)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find pneumonia patients via diagnosis codes. **First acute infection phenotype** (distinct from chronic HCV/HIV). Pneumonia is documented under multiple SNOMED codes by etiology and acquisition setting: parent pneumonia, community-acquired pneumonia (CAP), nosocomial (hospital-acquired), bacterial, and viral pneumonia.",
  "prompt": "Find all patients with a diagnosis of pneumonia, including community-acquired pneumonia, nosocomial (hospital-acquired) pneumonia, bacterial pneumonia, and viral pneumonia.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with pneumonia.",
    "broad": "Find all patients diagnosed with any form of pneumonia — including the parent pneumonia concept, community-acquired pneumonia (CAP), nosocomial/hospital-acquired pneumonia, bacterial pneumonia, and viral pneumonia.",
    "expert": "I need to identify all pneumonia patients. Pneumonia is documented under multiple SNOMED codes by etiology: Pneumonia (233604007) is the parent concept, Community acquired pneumonia (385093006), Nosocomial pneumonia (425464007), Bacterial pneumonia (53084003), and Viral pneumonia (75570004). Search Condition resources for all five codes."
  },
